Posts.Content: Mar 22, 2010 08:44PM - edited Mar 22, 2010 08:45PM by Mei I had a cluster of microcalcifications with 4-B(No lump and mess) seen on a digital mammogram last month. It was in my left breast and close to chest wall. I got an open excisional biopsy to take it out, and got the B9 result last week. My doctor told me 80% turns out to be B9. Don't worry, wish you have a B9 result.
